commentPostTextItems.html: They will be pleased as punch with this performance

Their batting never really took off in the face of some good bowling by England's seamers, some rash strokes were responsible for wickets at regular intervals, only Harbhajan with a spirited 37 lifted them to 203
In the end though it was too much for England, who also got off to a horrible start as Pathan nabbed out to early wickets
Flintoff and Pietersen led a fightback but Dravid backed his spinners, and Harbhajan finished with a career-best 5 for 31, what a match he had
Yuvraj chipped in with two wickets as well
India take a 1-0 lead in the series
Harbhajan is the righful Man-of-the-Match for his 37 and 5-31 later in the day, a great allround performance from him

"It feels great to be back in the wickets...its been a while and it really is special...i was confident of getting back and God was kind to me today, I bounced back with five wickets...thanks to all who kept faith in me"
Flintoff hopefull of bouncing back in the next game

Dravid: "i dont think we batted well at all, 203 was not enough...but harbhajan bowled brilliantly...and Irfan bowled some very good first overs for us....once you put people under pressure strange things happen....harbhajan did excellently well today, he also scored those 37 vital runs...
Thats all from the presentation ceremony, hope youve enjoyed this match
